reviews.review_text:
Excellent Matrix One of the best shows from the 2nd half of 78. Love the sound on this, right around this time the sbds start sounding a little dry to me, I prefer the sound on this over the Road Trips release... this recording has great clarity & ambiance. Hunter Seamons makes a great matrix!

2nd set gets it done..nice extended jam out of estimated, great He's Gone, Mojo seems a little 'stuck' at times & drawn out but there's still some great stuff in there..Jerry's guitar is on the 'prowl' as they dive into the Other One which is full of energy...which drops into a noteworthy Stella. There are better shows from the year but this is worth your time.
